data.enText: -ies

data.chText: 领土；版图；领地
data.enText: land that is under the control of a particular country or ruler

data.chText: 敌方 / 有争议的 / 外国领土
data.enText: enemy/disputed/foreign territory

data.chText: 被占领的土地
data.enText: occupied territories

data.chText: 他们拒不允许联合国部队驻扎在他们的国土上。
data.enText: They have refused to allow UN troops to be stationed in their territory.

data.chText: （个人、群体、动物等占据的）领域，管区，地盘
data.enText: an area that one person, group, animal, etc. considers as their own and defends against others who try to enter it

data.chText: 乌鸫交配时会保护自己的地盘，不允许外来者侵入。
data.enText: Mating blackbirds will defend their territory against intruders.

data.chText: 我们从未涉足过这类工作。
data.enText: This type of work is uncharted territory for us.

data.chText: 法律问题由安迪负责处理。
data.enText: Legal problems are Andy's territory (= he deals with them) .

data.chText: （某人负责的）地区
data.enText: an area of a town, country, etc. that sb has responsibility for in their work or another activity

data.chText: 我们的代理人负责的地区很广。
data.enText: Our representatives cover a very large territory.

data.chText: （某类）地区；（某种）地方
data.enText: a particular type of land

data.chText: 未勘察地区
data.enText: unexplored territory

data.chText: （美国）准州；（澳大利亚）地区；（加拿大）地区
data.enText: a country or an area that is part of the US, Australia or Canada but is not a state or province

data.chText: 关岛和美属萨摩亚是美国的准州。
data.enText: Guam and American Samoa are US territories.
come/go with the territory

data.chText: 成为必然的部分（或结果）
data.enText: to be a normal and accepted part of a particular job, situation, etc.

data.chText: 她在大部分日子里都得工作到很晚，但根据她的工作性质，这是不可避免的。
data.enText: She has to work late most days, but in her kind of job that goes with the territory.
on neutral ground/territory

data.chText: 在中立地区；在第三方地区
data.enText: in a place that has no connection with either of the people or sides who are meeting and so does not give an advantage to either of them

data.chText: 我们决定在第三方领土上会晤。
data.enText: We decided to meet on neutral ground.

tr: an area of knowledge or interest
example: his questions covered a lot of territory

tr: the geographical area under the jurisdiction of a sovereign state
example: American troops were stationed on Japanese soil

tr: a region marked off for administrative or other purposes

value.def: Territory is land which is controlled by a particular country or ruler.

example.ex: The government denies that any of its territory is under rebel control.
example.tran: 政府否认有领土被反叛分子所控制。

value.def: A territory is a country or region that is controlled by another country.

example.ex: They just want to return to their families in the occupied territories...
example.tran: 他们只是想回到在占领区的家人身边。

example.ex: He toured some of the disputed territories now under UN control.
example.tran: 他去一些目前由联合国接管的争议地区巡视了一番。

value.tran: 属地，地区，托管地(指被别国控制的国家或地区)

value.def: You can use territory to refer to an area of knowledge or experience.

example.ex: Following the futuristic The Handmaid's Tale, Margaret Atwood's seventh novel, Cat's Eye, returns to more familiar territory...
example.tran: 写完了具有未来色彩的《女仆的故事》之后，玛格丽特·阿特伍德的第七部小说《猫眼》回归到了人们较熟悉的题材上。

example.ex: Reading from a tedious technical brief for hours on end, he would stray into difficult territory.
example.tran: 连续看上几个小时枯燥的技术简报后，他会不自觉地钻起牛角尖来。

value.def: An animal's territory is an area which it regards as its own and which it defends when other animals try to enter it.

example.ex: The territory of a cat only remains fixed for as long as the cat dominates the area.
example.tran: 猫的地盘只在它占据那个地方的时候是固定不变的。

value.def: Territory is land with a particular character.
If you say that something comes with the territory, you mean that you accept it as a natural result of the situation you are in.

example.ex: Doing human rights work is risky business. That comes with the territory...
example.tran: 做人权工作是要冒风险的。这是难免的。

example.ex: You can't expect not to have a debate; that's what comes with the territory in a democracy.
example.tran: 不要指望不会发生辩论，那在民主社会已成为必然。

value.tran: 是难免的事;是必然的事
